    Scope and Contents
Virginia, wife of the late Jack W. Loftus, describes his service in Decatur City government for 25 years as an elected and appointed official: the Council/Manager and Commission forms of city government; city politics; and problems of retirement. Also discusses her life and family in Decatur. 2 tapes, 120 mins., 41 pp. 
Interview by Mark W. Sorensen, 1978 
